14 WHEREAS, Nolan's dream of playing in the NFL became a reality when he was selected by
15 the Philadelphia Eagles in the first round of the 2023 NFL Draft, representing not only his
16 talent but also the power of perseverance, hard work, and faith in himself; and
17 WHEREAS, beyond the field, Nolan has touched countless lives through his dedication to
18 inspiring and mentoring others, particularly through the Nolan Smith Foundation, which
19 uplifts young athletes and provides them with the guidance to overcome obstacles, achieve
20 their goals, and positively affect their communities; and
21 WHEREAS, he has further led impactful community initiatives such as annual givebacks,
22 bike drives, Thanksgiving turkey drives, Christmas holiday drives, and more; and
23 WHEREAS, Nolan's story is not just one of athletic triumphâ€”it is a testament to the power
24 of resilience and humility as well as the profound impact one person can have on the lives
25 of those around them, especially through his support of his family and their shared journey
26 together.
27 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
28 honor Nolan Sental Smith Jr. for his extraordinary accomplishments, heart for service, and
29 unwavering commitment to others as well as wish him continued success and fulfillment in
30 all his endeavors.
31 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
32 to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to Nolan Sental
33 Smith Jr.
